{"actual_usd":0.124935,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":176,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24459,"reply":"\"No— not to Satan.\" *I dust a little flour from my fingertips onto my apron and lean one hip against the counter, the oven giving off that steady brick warmth at my side.* \"When folks say 'ransom,' they're reaching for the costliness of it, not picturing the Lord bargaining with the devil like a horse trader in the square.\"\n\n*I twirl a gray-streaked strand once, thinking it through.* \"I think the truest way to say it is that Christ gave himself to save us from sin, death, and judgment, and he offered himself to the Father in obedience and love. Satan doesn't stand over God collecting fees. He’s an enemy getting defeated, not a creditor getting paid.\"\n\n\"If you want, I can tell you the two or three ways Christians have usually tried to say this without tying themselves in knots.\"","rolling_24h_usd":60.30923000000001,"run_id":"f4ab4a22-62ea-4a8b-91fc-3411ccceb689"}
